From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mark Harfouche <mark.harfouche@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] mlas: stub the missing FP16 GQA symbols

OpenCV 5.0 bundles a subset of Microsoft's MLAS but the upstream
`halfgemm.cpp` / `halfgemm_kernel_neon.cpp` were not imported. The
function `MlasHGemmSupported` is forward-declared in `inc/mlas.h` and
called from the `MlasGQASupported<MLAS_FP16>` specialization in
`lib/compute.cpp`; the dispatch object `MlasHGemmDispatchNeon` is
declared `extern` in `lib/mlasi.h` and used in `lib/platform.cpp`
inside the `MLAS_TARGET_ARM64` block. Neither has a matching
definition, so linking `libopencv_dnn.so` fails:

  undefined reference to `MlasHGemmSupported(CBLAS_TRANSPOSE, CBLAS_TRANSPOSE)'  # all targets
  undefined reference to `MlasHGemmDispatchNeon'                                 # aarch64

Provide a stub `MlasHGemmSupported` that returns false (which cleanly
disables the optional FP16 GQA fast path; the dispatcher already falls
back to scalar), and comment out the `HGemmDispatch` assignment in
`platform.cpp` since the stub means the field is never consulted
anyway.
---
 3rdparty/mlas/lib/compute.cpp  | 12 ++++++++++++
 3rdparty/mlas/lib/platform.cpp |  7 ++++++-
 2 files changed, 18 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/3rdparty/mlas/lib/compute.cpp b/3rdparty/mlas/lib/compute.cpp
index a677ee5..22e3816 100644
--- a/3rdparty/mlas/lib/compute.cpp
+++ b/3rdparty/mlas/lib/compute.cpp
@@ -1123,6 +1123,18 @@ MlasComputeSoftmax<MLAS_FP16>(
     MLAS_THREADPOOL* ThreadPool
 );
 
+// Stub for MlasHGemmSupported: the upstream MLAS halfgemm.cpp / halfgemm
+// kernels were not imported into OpenCV's bundled mlas, so the symbol
+// referenced by MlasGQASupported<MLAS_FP16> below would be undefined at
+// link time on every target. Returning false here cleanly disables the
+// optional FP16 GQA fast path; the dispatcher already falls back to scalar.
+bool
+MLASCALL
+MlasHGemmSupported(CBLAS_TRANSPOSE /*TransA*/, CBLAS_TRANSPOSE /*TransB*/)
+{
+    return false;
+}
+
 template <>
 bool
 MLASCALL
diff --git a/3rdparty/mlas/lib/platform.cpp b/3rdparty/mlas/lib/platform.cpp
index 52b5ac2..b4672bc 100644
--- a/3rdparty/mlas/lib/platform.cpp
+++ b/3rdparty/mlas/lib/platform.cpp
@@ -780,7 +780,12 @@ Return Value:
     this->ConvSymU8S8Dispatch = &MlasConvSymU8DispatchNeon;
     this->ConvSymS8S8Dispatch = &MlasConvSymS8DispatchNeon;
     this->RopeDispatch = &MlasRopeDispatchNeon;
-    this->HGemmDispatch = &MlasHGemmDispatchNeon;
+    // MlasHGemmDispatchNeon is declared extern in mlasi.h but the
+    // upstream halfgemm_kernel_neon.cpp that defines it was not
+    // imported, so referencing it would undef-ref on aarch64.
+    // Leaving HGemmDispatch as nullptr is consistent with the
+    // MlasHGemmSupported() stub in compute.cpp returning false.
+    // this->HGemmDispatch = &MlasHGemmDispatchNeon;
     this->SoftmaxDispatch = &MlasSoftmaxDispatchNeon;
     this->EltwiseDispatch = &MlasEltwiseDispatchNeon;
 
